# 👓 Smart Glasses for the Visually Challenged


The Smart Glasses for Visually Challenged is an assistive wearable device designed to empower visually impaired individuals 
by enhancing their perception of the surrounding environment. This project integrates advanced technologies such as 
real-time object detection, optical character recognition (OCR), and audio feedback to provide continuous environmental 
awareness and improve mobility and independence
---

## 🚀 Features

- 🔍 **Real-time Object Detection** using YOLOv5
- 📖 **Text Recognition** with Tesseract OCR
- 🗣️ **Environment Description** using NLP & gTTS (Text to Speech)
- 🎥 **Raspberry Pi 4** integration for on-the-go computing
- 🎧 Audio Output through earphones for real-time feedback

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- Python, OpenCV, YOLOv5
- Tesseract OCR, gTTS
- Raspberry Pi, NLP
- LangChain (for description generation)
- Hardware: Pi Camera, Buzzer, Smart Glass Frame




